question_text: What thing, person or moment filled you with gratitude recently?
What went well recently and why?
How are you feeling? Mind and body
If you dream, what would you like to dream about tonight?
How was your time management recently? Anything to improve?
Relationshipwise, which is going well or which needs more attention?
How have you handled criticism recently? Positively or Negatively?
When was your last meditative/spiritual moment? How did you feel?
When was the last time you were outdoors? What was enjoyable about it?
What is something new you learned about yourself recently?
When did you feel most focused yesterday or today, and what helped you get there?
What motivates you most about your career or daily work right now?
What personal boundary have you set recently, and how has it helped you?
What challenge have you been mentally avoiding because it feels too big or too uncertain?
What is something you feel lucky to have in your life?
Did you notice any negative thought patterns lately, and how did you handle them?
What progress have you made recently towards your health?
What is your "go-to" book, movie or show? Why?
Were you satisfied with what you accomplished today or yesterday?
Who made you feel supported or understood recently, and how did they do so?
What was your most recent failure? Were you able to bounce back?
When did you last feel truly at peace, and what created that feeling?
How did time spent outdoors (or lack of it) affect you recently?
Have you felt more present in the moment recently, or more distracted—why?
How would you describe the balance between work, rest, and play in your life right now?
When you feel embarrassed, do you tend to laugh it off, hide it, or replay it in your mind?
Which risk did you take lately that you are thankful for?
What is something about your current self that your younger self would admire?
How has your body felt throughout the day recently—energized, tired, tense, or relaxed?
What is a consistent and reliable source of joy for you?
Name an obstacle to your goals… Why is it hindering you?
When did you recently feel alone, even while around other people—and what made it feel that way?
What recurring worry or fear has been on your mind lately?
When you scroll social media, what emotion usually shows up first—envy, excitement, boredom, validation, or something else?
How connected have you felt to your community or the world around you recently?
How has your meals affected your mood or energy recently? Is a change needed?
Did you notice a moment of beauty recently—natural, artistic, or human?
Are you feeling overall stagnant or are you progressing towards a goal?
Did you notice any moments of self-doubt recently, and how did you respond?
Have you compared yourself to someone online recently—what specifically triggered that comparison?
Where in your life do you succeed behind the scenes without validation?
In what ways did you move your body recently, and how did it make you feel?
What is the most recent moment you genuinely felt proud—even if no one else cared?
Are your distractions giving you relief or just postponing discomfort?
If you reduced your time online this week, what might you gain back in your life?
If you could remove one distraction for the next 7 days, which one would create the biggest change?
What are you proud of that doesn't look impressive on paper?
When was the last time you pushed through discomfort, and what did you learn about yourself?
What is the distraction you keep going back to, even when you know it derails your focus?
How has your eating been tied to emotion lately—comfort, boredom, stress, celebration?
When were you most distracted in the last 48 hours, and what were you avoiding in that moment?
What belief about food or diet is no longer serving you?
What environment helps you stay focused—and when did you last put yourself in it?
What version of yourself (past or present) deserves more recognition from you?
